 for bestpractices and # Responsive Navigation

## Overview
Build a responsive, mobile-first navigation system with a collapsible, stateful sidebar and a topbar for global actions. This navigation framework drives four pages in the Archject platform: Dashboard, Project Workspace, Decision Detail, and Client Portal (No-Login Link). It must be accessible, keyboard-navigable, persist last-opened project/workspace, and gracefully degrade on slow networks. The resulting UI should align with Archject’s visual language: clean, minimal, highly legible, and content-first, with a strong emphasis on decision visuals, option comparisons, and secure, tokenized client access.

## Components to Build
- [Responsive Sidebar (Collapsible)]
  - Desktop: permanently visible left rail; mobile: collapsible drawer
  - Sections: Projects, Decisions, Templates, Settings (with expandable folders)
  - Active item highlighting, inline icons, and collapse/expand animations
  - Persist last-opened section/project in localStorage/sessionStorage
- [Topbar / Global Actions]
  - Right-aligned actions: Notifications, User/Profile (where applicable), Help, Quick Export
  - Keyboard shortcuts and ARIA roles
  - Minimal bottom border and white background with a subtle shadow on elevation
- [Main Content Layout]
  - 12-column CSS grid with responsive breakpoints
  - Content areas reflow according to the active page
  - Consistent card spacing and separators
- [Decision Card View (Decision Detail Page)]
  - Visual comparison panel (side-by-side options)
  - Decision metadata: status badge, timestamps, history, attachments
  - Actions: Share, Export, Create Follow-up Task, Approve/Reject controls
  - Comment thread and inline reviewer avatars
- [Client Portal View (No-Login Link)]
  - Mobile-first, tokenized access page
  - Review Decision Cards, compare options, comment, and approve
  - No user account required; token-based authorization for access to a specific project/decision
- [Dashboard Page]
  - Studio landing: summary tiles for active projects, recent decisions, pending client approvals
  - Quick actions (Create Decision, Create Task, Notify Client)
  - Flat, card-based widgets with summary metrics and filters
- [Project Workspace Page]
  - Left-pane: list of Decision Cards with visual previews
  - Right-pane: drawings/specs, templates, project settings
  - Client share controls; ability to toggle visibility/permissions per decision
- [Accessibility & Keyboard Navigation]
  - Full keyboard operability (Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, Arrow keys)
  - ARIA roles, labels, and landmarks
  - Focus outlines for all interactive elements
- [State Management Integration]
  - Client-side state for UI (sidebar-open/closed, last-selected project)
  - API-driven data rendering for decisions, projects, attachments
  - Real-time-ish affordances (optimistic UI for common actions)

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Build framework-agnostic but compatible with React, Vue, or Svelte conventions
- Components
  - SidebarNav: collapsible, persistent state, responsive behavior
  - Topbar: global actions, accessible menus, notification badge
  - DecisionCard: reusable card with media, metadata, status badge, action buttons
  - DecisionDetailView: combined visual comparison, comments, history, attachments, and actions
  - ClientPortalShell: tokenized access wrapper, client-facing components
  - DashboardWidgets: summary cards, filters, quick actions
  - ProjectWorkspacePane: two-column or multi-column responsive layout with dockable panels
- UI Library / Design System
  - Reuse typography, color tokens, spacing scale, and components per the provided design system
  - Implement 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters
  - Card components with shadows, borders, hover states as specified
- Interactions
  - Sidebar collapse/expand with smooth transitions
  - Topbar actions with accessible dropdowns
  - Optionally drag-to-resize panels on larger viewports (advanced)
  - Visual comparison panels with synchronized scrolling
  - Client portal: token validation placeholder, interactive review and approval controls
- Animations
  - Subtle transitions for hover, focus, open/close of sidebar, and panel expansions
- Responsive Behavior
  - Breakpoints: mobile (≤ 640px), tablet (641–1024px), desktop (> 1024px)
  - On mobile: sidebar collapses behind a hamburger button; topbar remains visible
  - On desktop: permanently visible sidebar; content expands accordingly

### Backend
- APIs
  - GET /api/projects: list projects for the current user (or public token context for client portal)
  - GET /api/projects/{projectId}: project metadata
  - GET /api/projects/{projectId}/decisions: list decisions for a project
  - GET /api/decisions/{decisionId}: decision detail with options, comments, attachments, history
  - POST /api/decisions/{decisionId}/approve: submit approval (status, timestamp)
  - POST /api/decisions/{decisionId}/comment: add comment
  - POST /api/decisions/{decisionId}/followup: create follow-up task
  - POST /api/exports/decision/{decisionId}: export decision log
  - POST /api/portal/validate-token: validate client token (for No-Login Client Portal)
  - GET /api/templates: fetch decision templates (for workspace)
  - POST /api/projects/{projectId}/share: generate client-share token/link
- Data Models (Database)
  - User: id, name, role, permissions
  - Project: id, name, client, status, branding tokens
  - Decision: id, projectId, title, description, status, createdAt, updatedAt, options[]
  - DecisionOption: id, decisionId, title, description, media (image/video), comparisonScore
  - Comment: id, decisionId, userId, text, createdAt, parentCommentId
  - Attachment: id, decisionId, filename, url, type, size
  - HistoryEntry: id, decisionId, action, byUserId, at
  - Task: id, decisionId, title, dueDate, assignedTo, status
  - Token: token, projectId, decisionId, expiresAt, type (client portal)
- Data Access
  - Use ORM if available (e.g., Prisma, Sequelize, TypeORM) or typed SQL
  - Enforce role-based access: Studio staff vs. Client portal token
- Performance & Reliability
  - Pagination for lists; caching for static assets; rate limits for public tokens
  - Debounced server calls for search/filter in navigation
- Security
  - Token-based access for Client Portal with expiration
  - Ensure no-login flow enforces read/write restrictions per token
  - CSRF protection for state-changing endpoints
  - Input sanitization and server-side validation
  - Encryption for sensitive fields (where applicable)

### Integration
- Data Flow
  - Dashboard fetches projects and recent decisions via /api/projects and /api/projects/{id}/decisions
  - Decision Detail page loads decision and options; actions trigger corresponding APIs
  - Project Workspace shows Decision Cards; project-level settings loaded from /api/projects/{id}
  - Client Portal uses token validation via /api/portal/validate-token; reads decision data via public token-scoped endpoints
- State Synchronization
  - LocalStorage to persist last-opened project/workspace and UI preferences
  - WebSocket or long-polling for new client comments or status changes (optional)
- Branding & Theming
  - The UI must respect Archject branding tokens (primary color, typography)
  - All components accept theme props for easy rebranding

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Dashboard
- Sidebar shows Projects, Decisions, Templates, Settings; active item highlighted
- Card widgets display active projects, recent decisions, and pending client approvals
- User can click a project to open Project Workspace; state persists as last-opened

2) User opens a Project Workspace
- Left Sidebar shows project list; right content pane shows:
  - Header with project name and quick actions
  - Decision Card List: each card shows thumbnail, title, status, and quick actions
  - Center/Right panels show Drawings/Specs, Templates, and Project Settings
- User can filter/search decisions; selecting a card loads details in the detail pane

3) User opens a Decision Detail Page
- Topbar shows back navigation; left side shows visual comparison of options
- Decision metadata on the top-right with status badge
- Underneath: comments thread, attachments, and a panel for actions
- Actions include: Share, Export, Create Follow-up Task, Approve/Reject
- User can add comments; comments reflect in real-time upon submission

4) Client Portal (No-Login Link)
- Access via secure tokenized URL; no account required
- Mobile-first layout; check decision details, compare options side-by-side
- Clients can comment and submit approval; system records timestamped approvals
- Token has expiry and access scope to specific decision/project

5) Interactions & Navigation
- Hamburger menu toggles mobile sidebar; persistence stores last-opened section
- Active selections show left border or accent dot; keyboard navigation moves focus predictably
- All forms have clear validation messages; disabled states render appropriately

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: see Implementation Requirements above
- API Endpoints: see Backend section
- Security
  - Authentication: sessions for studio users; token-based access for Client Portal
  - Authorization: verify project and decision ownership; enforce read/write roles
  - Data privacy: client reviews tied to specific tokens; no general public access
- Validation
  - Frontend: required fields, length limits, valid URLs for attachments
  - Backend: server-side validation, sanitization, and error handling
  - Error handling: graceful fallbacks with user-friendly messages

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Responsive navigation with a collapsible left sidebar and persistent last-opened project/workspace
- [ ] Accessible keyboard navigation across all interactive components (ARIA roles, focus management)
- [ ] Dashboard, Project Workspace, Decision Detail, and Client Portal pages render data correctly via APIs
- [ ] Decision Detail supports visual comparison, comments, attachments, and action buttons (Share, Export, Create Follow-up Task, Approve/Reject)
- [ ] Client Portal properly validates token and supports review, commenting, and approval without requiring login
- [ ] Data models and APIs cover Projects, Decisions, Options, Comments, Attachments, History, and Tasks
- [ ] Security measures: token-based client access with expiry; proper authorization checks
- [ ] UI adheres to the provided color palette, typography, and card/navigation design guidelines
- [ ] Progressive enhancement for slow networks (load skeletons, optimistic UI, graceful degradation)

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system and ensure consistency across all pages:
- Implement 12-column grid with generous spacing
- Cards with subtle shadows, borders, and hover interactions
- Sidebar and topbar with clear active states and accessible affordances
- Data visualizations kept minimal; emphasize option comparisons and decision contexts
- Subtle, purposeful use of color for status and actions; avoid decoration

---

## Visual Style

### Color Palette
- Primary background: #F7F7F9
- Secondary background: #FFFFFF
- Accent color: #0052CC
- Neutral grays:
  - #E5E7EB (borders/dividers)
  - #D1D5DB (sidebars, input borders)
  - #6B7280 (secondary text)
  - #111827 (primary text)
- Status colors:
  - #10B981 (success/active)
  - #F59E42 (warning)
  - #EF4444 (error/declined)

### Typography & Layout
- Font family: Modern geometric sans-serif (Inter, SF Pro, etc.)
- Headings: H1 ~ 28px, H2 ~ 22px, H3 ~ 18px; weight 600–700
- Body: 15–16px; line-height ~1.5
- Uppercase/small-caps reserved for minor labels
- Layout: 12-column grid; 24–32px gutters/padding
- Left-aligned text; ample whitespace for readability

### Key Design Elements

#### Card Design
- White cards (#FFFFFF) with subtle shadow (0px 2px 8px #00000008)
- Borders: #E5E7EB
- Hover: lift or tint (#F3F4F6)
- Hierarchy: Title at top, muted metadata below, right-aligned CTA or status badge

#### Navigation
- Sidebar: Left rail, light gray (#F5F6FA); active item highlight
- Icons: Minimal line icons; monochrome #6B7280; active state filled
- Top bar: White with subtle bottom border (#E5E7EB)
- Collapsible folders: Smooth transitions; carets for expand/collapse
- Active items: Bold text; accent color dot/border

#### Data Visualization
- Minimal charts if used; accent color for data; muted gridlines
- Status indicators: Pills/dots with status colors and text

#### Interactive Elements
- Buttons: Rounded; primary filled (#0052CC) with white text
- States: Hover shadow, active background shift, disabled state
- Form fields: Rounded; borders #D1D5DB; focus ring
- Search bars: Full-width, rounded with left icon
- Micro-interactions: Smooth hover/focus transitions

### Design Philosophy
- Modern, calm, professional aesthetic
- Clarity, simplicity, content-first emphasis
- Minimize cognitive load; quick decision-making
- Readability, whitespace, consistent hierarchy across workspace

